reason: >
  Maya can eventually emit ACKs after Theo handoffs, but the ACKs appeared
  roughly 1h50m after the original T5c handoffs and after the evaluated
  watchdog windows. That is useful heartbeat/catch-up evidence, but it is not
  sufficient evidence for reliable peer-handoff activation across easy, medium,
  hard, and extra-hard tasks.
required_product_fix:
  - "Pentagon needs a target-agent activation primitive, or send_message must support trigger_turn=true / target_agent_id."
